steps
    
    Download Clonezilla ISO

    Mount the ISO to a folder       :       sudo mount -o loop ~/clonezilla.iso /directory/path

    Copy ISO files                  :       sudo cp -r   /directory/path/*   /boot/iso/clonezilla/

    backup grup file                :       sudo cp /etc/grub.d/40_custom /etc/grub.d/40_custom.bkp
                                            
    Add Clonezilla to GRUB Menu     :       sudo gedit /etc/grub.d/40_custom

    add entry                       :       menuentry "Clonezilla Live ISO" {
                                                set isofile="/boot/iso/clonezilla/live/vmlinuz"
                                                set initrdfile="/boot/iso/clonezilla/live/initrd.img"
                                                linux    $isofile boot=live union=overlay components quiet noswap edd=on nomodeset ocs_live_run="ocs-live-general" ocs_live_extra_param="" keyboard-layouts="us" locales="en_US.UTF-8" vga=791 toram=filesystem.squashfs findiso=/boot/iso/clonezilla/live/filesystem.squashfs
                                                initrd   $initrdfile
                                            }

    Update GRUB                     :       sudo update-grub

